primer
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:one of the primer classes, covering the first years of instruction in a primary school; also, a child in a primer class. (Probably derived from <i>primer</i> `elementary reading book', OED2, which is also in common use in NZ.)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:with short i
Notes: with short i	incl primers, the primers
